The paper presents a pruning algorithm for neural networks that is computationally efficient, provably accurate, and broadly applicable to various network architectures and data distributions. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). However, given the focus on neural networks and their optimization, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper's empirical comparisons and experimental results also suggest a focus on practical applications, which further supports the likelihood of cs.LG and cs.AI as the primary sub-categories.
